  "prompt": "What are the biggest questions that are yet inanswered in the theory of evolution?",
  "response": "While evolutionary theory is well-established, several significant questions remain:\n\n1. Mechanisms of Evolution\n- Exact details of speciation processes\n- Complete understanding of epigenetic inheritance\n- Precise mechanisms of genetic mutation rates\n\n2. Major Transitions\n- Origin of complex multicellular life\n- Emergence of eukaryotic cells\n- Initial development of complex cellular machinery\n- Precise steps in the transition from single-celled to multicellular organisms\n\n3. Evolutionary Complexity\n- How complex biological structures evolve\n- Detailed mechanisms of convergent evolution\n- Complete explanation of punctuated equilibrium\n\n4. Genetic/Molecular Questions\n- Full understanding of gene regulation\n- Complete mapping of evolutionary relationships between species\n- Precise mechanisms of horizontal gene transfer\n\n5. Early Life Origins\n- Exact chemical processes that led to first self-replicating molecules\n- Conditions that sparked initial biological evolution\n- Transition from chemical to biological systems\n\n6. Human Evolution\n- Precise genetic pathways of human brain development\n- Complete understanding of human migration patterns\n- Detailed mechanisms of human-specific adaptations\n\n7. Evolutionary Developmental Biology\n- How genetic changes produce morphological variations\n- Complete understanding of developmental constraints\n\nThese areas represent active research frontiers where scientists continue exploring and refining evolutionary understanding.",
